\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Watermark evasion analysis across three strategies: paraphrasing (synonym substitution intensity $\rho \in [0.1, 0.5]$), copy-paste dilution (dilution ratio $r \in [0.5, 3.0]$), and adaptive character substitution (budget $b \in [1, 20]$). The unigram z-score defense maintains $\text  {TPR}= 1.00$ across all tested intensity levels on the synthetic corpus; the embedded vocabulary bias survives these mild evasion strategies. (Table~\ref {tab:evasion}; detailed z-score distributions in Appendix~\ref {sec:evasion_appendix}.)}}{18}{figure.caption.50}\protected@file@percent }
